As large organisations may be comprised of many interacting portfolios, the guild system enables portfolios to align to the organisation's overall business strategy, market position and technical choices while maintaining their respective [[autonomy|Autonomy]].

Guilds are meetings held to maintain alignment between [[Portfolio]]s on crosscutting concerns outside the normal [[chapter|Chapter Meeting]] competencies. They may also be used to coordinate chapters across Portfolios. 